  * Added "Provides: amarok*", for users who whant packages that depend on Amarok. 

 -- Bogdan Butnaru <bogdanb@gmail.com>  Mon, 08 Jun 2009 00:31:30 +0200

amarok (2:1.4.10-0ubuntu3~ppa2) jaunty; urgency=low

  * Fix of Wikipedia display in context browser, suggested by WarwichH at https://bugs.edge.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/amarok/+bug/316140/comments/4. Thanks to Kevin K (https://edge.launchpad.net/~stafio) for the hint.

 -- Bogdan Butnaru <bogdanb@gmail.com>  Sun, 05 Apr 2009 16:37:39 +0200

amarok (2:1.4.10-0ubuntu3~ppa1) jaunty; urgency=low

  * Re-release of Amarok series 1.4
  * Suffixed all binary package names with '14', to prevent apt from
    replacing them with the 2.* series in the repositories
  * Removed some components I don't use and don't have time to figure out:
    - only Xine engine was kept
    - install-mp3 is removed, the Xine engine now depends on it
    - debug binaries are out
  * Added 'Conflicts' on the non-suffixed version of the packages, so you 
    can't have both series of Amarok installed at the same time
  * Be careful, I didn't test this very much; make a back-up of your library
    before trying it
  * Patches are welcome  	

 -- Bogdan Butnaru <bogdanb@gmail.com>  Tue, 10 Feb 2009 17:04:16 +0100

amarok (2:1.4.10-0ubuntu3) intrepid; urgency=low

  * Add kubuntu_12_eject_command.diff, change eject command to
    umount, we no longer have kdeeject

